<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: after-white-space;"><p =
data-start=3D"410" data-end=3D"421">Hi Grant,</p><p data-start=3D"423" =
data-end=3D"541">Thank you for your recent email following our meeting. =
I appreciate your efforts in summarising the agreed next steps.</p><p =
data-start=3D"543" data-end=3D"800">I would like to remind you few =
&nbsp;key issues that remain unresolved. These relate to the contents =
assessment (including electronic items and my electric vehicle), the =
scope of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s involvement, and the ongoing handling =
of the property claim.</p><h3 data-section-id=3D"1ex3y92" =
data-start=3D"807" data-end=3D"872"><br></h3><h3 =
data-section-id=3D"1ex3y92" data-start=3D"807" =
data-end=3D"872">1.&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"814" =
data-end=3D"872">Assessment of Retained Electronic Items and EV =
Vehicle</strong></h3><p data-start=3D"874" data-end=3D"1222">As =
discussed at the outset with both Chris and Sasha =E2=80=94 and =
reiterated again during our meeting =E2=80=94 I took &nbsp;items from =
the property, including mobile devices, laptops, and tablets. In =
addition, my&nbsp;<span data-start=3D"1107" data-end=3D"1132">electric =
vehicle (EV)</span>&nbsp;was on the premises at the time of the incident =
and contains a large lithium-ion battery.</p><p data-start=3D"1224" =
data-end=3D"1477">These &nbsp;items have been exposed to heat or smoke. =
While they may appear unaffected externally, I remain seriously =
concerned about internal damage, battery integrity, and the potential =
risk of delayed failure or fire.</p><p data-start=3D"1479" =
data-end=3D"1590">Your response, which places the onus on me to arrange =
testing, is not sufficient in this context. Specifically.&nbsp;<span =
data-start=3D"1593" data-end=3D"1745">Tower must take responsibility for =
verifying the safety of these items =E2=80=94 especially the EV =E2=80=94 =
given the potential safety risk to people and property and still need to =
assesss if those need to be restored or replaced. It is likely that =
could be smoke or damage inside.</span></p><h3 data-section-id=3D"1bgefnz"=
 data-start=3D"2257" data-end=3D"2306">2.&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"2264"=
 data-end=3D"2306">Clarification of Asset Restore=E2=80=99s =
Scope</strong></h3><p data-start=3D"2308" data-end=3D"2485">Your email =
notes that Asset Restore will attend site to assess and remove =
fire-damaged contents and affected linings. Could you please clarify the =
following:</p><ul data-start=3D"2486" data-end=3D"2644"><li =
data-start=3D"2486" data-end=3D"2595"><p data-start=3D"2488" =
data-end=3D"2595">Will Asset Restore be removing fire- or smoke-damaged =
linings (e.g. jib and other non-structural elements)?</p></li><li =
data-start=3D"2596" data-end=3D"2644"><p data-start=3D"2598" =
data-end=3D"2644">Or is their role limited to contents =
handling?</p></li></ul><p data-start=3D"2646" data-end=3D"2755">This =
clarification is necessary to understand how and when a proper =
structural assessment will be undertaken.</p><h3 =
data-section-id=3D"1vrhk43" data-start=3D"2762" =
data-end=3D"2820">3.&nbsp;<strong data-start=3D"2769" =
data-end=3D"2820">House/Building Claim =E2=80=93 Request for Updated =
Plan</strong></h3><p data-start=3D"2822" data-end=3D"2978">In regards to =
the house claim. Could you please provide an updated &nbsp;and detailed =
plan, including:</p><ul data-start=3D"2979" data-end=3D"3179"><li =
data-start=3D"2979" data-end=3D"3055"><p data-start=3D"2981" =
data-end=3D"3055">A status update on the structural assessment and =
repair scope development;</p></li><li data-start=3D"3056" =
data-end=3D"3138"><p data-start=3D"3058" data-end=3D"3138">A timeline =
for each key stage: clearance, scoping, approval, tender, and =
repair;</p></li><li data-start=3D"3139" data-end=3D"3179"><p =
data-start=3D"3141" data-end=3D"3179">Named responsibilities for each =
stage.</p></li></ul><p data-start=3D"3181" data-end=3D"3353">Given the =
extent of damage and the disruption to my home, it is essential that I =
receive a clear, updated schedule of works and communication protocols =
for ongoing updates.</p><hr data-start=3D"3355" data-end=3D"3358"><p =
data-start=3D"3360" data-end=3D"3543">Please treat this as a formal and =
good-faith request for information and accountability. I would =
appreciate a written response addressing each of the above points as =
soon as possible.</p><p data-start=3D"3545" data-end=3D"3569">Kind =
regards,<br data-start=3D"3558" data-end=3D"3561">Rafaella</p><div =
class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" style=3D"direction: =
ltr;"><br><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 22 Jul 2025, at 12:19=E2=80=AF=
PM, Grant Metson &lt;Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz&gt; wrote:</div><br =
class=3D"Apple-interchange-newline"><div><meta charset=3D"UTF-8"><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Good =
afternoon Rafaella,<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">I wanted to take the time to =
thank you very much for meeting with Chris, David and myself at your =
place this afternoon. It was much =
appreciated.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">I felt that the meeting was =
very productive and positive as we all discussed the next steps and have =
agreed on the claim=E2=80=99s progression process moving =
forward.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;">I would like to re-confirm the next steps we agreed =
to in writing, and share with all as below:<o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><ol start=3D"1" type=3D"1" =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 0in; margin-top: 0in;"><li =
class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;">Asset Restore to attend site as soon as possible and =
complete the process of assessing and cataloging the contents for the =
response of the contents claim. After assessment the contents which are =
categorised as a total loss will be removed from =
site.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Asset =
Restore to strip out the property of any fire or smoke damaged linings =
or other non-structural items. This will enable a clear and clean =
structural assessment to be undertaken, from which we will produce a =
scope of works for the repairs required.<o:p></o:p></span></li><li =
class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;">Once we have a scope of works completed =E2=80=93 we will =
share this with you to approve before we submit to our repair panel for =
tendering.<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Confirming that you have =
notified us of the access code to be 1106.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">We will =
keep you updated on the above process and communicate with you as we =
move through the above steps.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin:=
 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">I have spoken with both our =
Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and they have said that the items you =
have enquired about are very unlikely to be affected by the fire given =
their location with respect to the proximity of the fire. I do =
understand that you would like to be 100% certain that the lithium =
batteries in these items have not been affected from the fire. The =
standard process in this situation is that you can undertake any testing =
of any of your items which you wish to, to obtain test results or a =
report which your insurer can consider for inclusion in your claims. If =
the test results prove any damage or loss to these items from the fire =
=E2=80=93 then your insurer will consider them within your =
claim.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: =
11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: =
Aptos, sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: =
0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">For contents items - please =
direct your enquiries to<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a =
href=3D"mailto:claims@tower.co.nz" style=3D"color: rgb(70, 120, 134); =
text-decoration: =
underline;">claims@tower.co.nz</a><o:p></o:p></span></div><div =
style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, =
sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">As you do =
not yet have a motor claim with Tower from this event =E2=80=93 you can =
also send any motor reports to<a href=3D"mailto:claims@tower.co.nz" =
style=3D"color: rgb(70, 120, 134); text-decoration: =
underline;">claims@tower.co.nz</a><span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span>and they will respond =
accordingly.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">Thank you again and I strongly =
encourage you to call me on the number below with any concerns that you =
have with the process of the claim =
progression.<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; =
font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span =
style=3D"font-family: Aptos, sans-serif;">All the =
best,<o:p></o:p></span></div><div style=3D"margin: 0in; font-size: 11pt; =
font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style=3D"font-family: Aptos, =
sans-serif;">Grant.<span =
class=3D"Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></span></div><tabl=
e class=3D"MsoNormalTable" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" =
cellpadding=3D"0" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse;"><tbody =
style=3D"caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; font-style: =
normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: =
normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; =
white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; =
text-decoration: none;"><tr style=3D"height: 126.75pt;"><td width=3D"243" =
style=3D"width: 182.25pt; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: =
126.75pt;"><div><br =
class=3D"webkit-block-placeholder"></div></td></tr></tbody></table></div><=
/blockquote></div><br></body></html>=

